    proc destroy_lexer from Lexer with lexer
    proc print_string with "  ✓ Label parser tests passed"
    proc print_newline
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies the parser handles a directive with an argument (.globl
main). Catches a regression where the parser expects directives to
be standalone or expects different argument grammar.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Tokenize ".globl main", parse. Assert ast is not null.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input ".globl main" -> non-null directive AST node, passed
- Parser rejects argument after directive -> ast == 0 -> "Directive parsed" fails
@End TestCases

Process called "test_parser_directive":
